            "currentCldrName": "Waning Crescent Moon",
            "description": "<p>A waning crescent moon (appearing to become smaller), the last of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_phase\">phases of the moon</a>. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its left side illuminated in a thin, golden or silver crescent, its remainder dark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>May be used to represent the moon more generally, nighttime, outer space, and astronomy. May also be used to convey enchanting or eerie feelings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In July 2023 this emoji trended on Emojipedia. This is likely due to it being required to complete developer Neal Agarwal&rsquo;s viral hit <a href=\"https://neal.fun/password-game/\">The Password Game</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See also <a href=\"/crescent-moon/\">ðŸŒ™&nbsp;Crescent Moon</a>. Not to be confused with <a href=\"/waxing-crescent-moon/\">ðŸŒ’&nbsp;Waxing Crescent Moon</a>, though their applications may overlap. Used as part of the <a href=\"https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/moon-emoji-creep\">Moon Emoji Creep</a> meme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung&rsquo;s design <a href=\"/samsung/experience-9.0/waning-crescent-moon/\">once</a> resembled a full moon with stars and <a href=\"/samsung/touchwiz-7.1/waning-crescent-moon/\">previously</a> displayed as a waning crescent moon in a night sky with stars.</p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"professor_prebid-root\">&nbsp;</div>",
